Instructions:
- Flat list of stories per increment
- No epic/sub-epic hierarchy shown
- Format: "- Actor --> Story Name"
- Stories listed in sequential order within increment
- Simple backlog view for sprint planning

## Increment {priority}: {increment_name}

(E) {epic_name}
    (E) {sub_epic_name}
        (S) {actor} --> {story_name}
        (S) {actor} --> {story_name}
        (S) {actor} --> {story_name}
    (E) {sub_epic_name}
        (E) {nested_sub_epic_name}
            (S) {actor} --> {story_name}
            (S) {actor} --> {story_name}

(E) {epic_name}
    (E) {sub_epic_name}
        (S) {actor} --> {story_name}

Instructions:
- Use (E) for Epics and Sub-Epics
- Use (S) for Stories with 'Actor --> Story Name' format
- Increments section uses FLAT story lists (no story groups, no connectors)
- Stories shown directly under sub-epics in sequential order
- Show actors with "--> " before story names
- Use hierarchical indentation (spaces, not tabs)
- Epic/Sub-Epic names: Verb-Noun format
- Story names: Actor-Verb-Noun format

